What is /root used for?-- /root is the home directory of the root user, who is the superuser (administrator) in a Linux system.

What is a user’s $PATH?--$PATH is an environment variable that tells the shell where to look for executable files when you run a command. echo $PATH

What various commands are used to extract files from an archive? -- TAR, UNZIP, GUNZIP

